 :tx/rationale "Create task: AUDIT-CALIBRATION: Improve task audit oracle to check acceptance criteria, not just spec coverage. BACKGROUND: Verification agents reviewed 15 audit-flagged tasks (70-100% confidence). Only 1/15 was actually implemented. The audit measures spec COVERAGE (do :impl/implements links exist for the task's spec refs?) but NOT task COMPLETION (are the specific acceptance criteria met?). A task requiring 'implement X with properties A, B, C, D' where only A and B exist gets flagged as 100% confidence. APPROACH: (1) Parse acceptance criteria from task body text (the ACCEPTANCE: section). (2) For each criterion, extract key identifiers (function names, type names, test names). (3) Search the codebase for those identifiers. (4) Confidence = (criteria_with_code_evidence / total_criteria). This gives COMPLETION confidence, not just COVERAGE confidence. (5) Display both scores: 'spec: 100% | criteria: 50%'. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Audit on a task with 4 criteria where 2 are implemented shows 50% criteria confidence. (B) Audit on a fully implemented task shows 100% for both. (C) Tasks with no ACCEPTANCE section fall back to spec-only scoring. TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-002, INV-WITNESS-011. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/task.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/task.rs."
